bluecherry (2.0.0-0beta1-5) lucid; urgency=low

  * This release incorporates beta1-4 changes (which was accidently made public, so some customers downloaded it - this the reason for the bump) along with these issues:

  * Bug #498: Server respawning in an endless loop
  * Bug #500: PHP Warning: SQLite3::query(): Unable to prepare statement: 1, unrecognized token: "0x00000002" in /usr/share/bluecherry/www/lib/lib.php on line 66
  * Bug #501: bc-detect showing other V4L devices
  * Bug #507: [Critical] Unable to playback events
  * Bug #509: [Critical] bc-server generating 584byte video files
  * Bug #510: MJPEG feed breaks, causing video weirdness on random ports
  * Bug #511: Error writing frame to outfile: Input/output error
  * Bug #513: bc-server segfaults and CPU soft locks
  * Bug #516: Web: Password changes do not take affect
  * Bug #518: Limit image width for motion mapping
  * Bug #519: bc-server crashes with E(1): asoundlib failed
  * Bug #520: audio_channels are not being added to the database
  * Feature #521: Add error logging for bc_alsa_open

  * Full list: http://improve.bluecherrydvr.com/versions/show/51

